<br>
cast in point, druids that quad kite from 30 to 65.  you could strip away every single ability except those they use for that one function and it wouldn't hinder them at all.  however, if you forced that druid into a healing role at 65 in PoP, well, i sure wouldn't want to be the tank he's responsible for.<br>
<br>
for versatility to work all options have to be equal and interchangeable depending on the situation.  i don't see that working in EQ, which is why, for most purposes, it is a game full of specialists.  even the &quot;versatile&quot; classes pick a specialty based on the person behind the character, the only difference is the specialty they pick, such as quad kiting, is a cross-section of the other roles and other misc. bits and pieces.  it is no broader than the other more generally recognized &quot;specialties&quot; though <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2599<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 11:21:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=424.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> I am still analyzing your essay, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Goladus</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and will have appropriate feedback when ready.<br>
